# UV per face corner (PRD 46): each face gets its own independent vt block,
# never shared with another face. The two octagon caps get a radial mapping
# derived from each vertex's actual (x, z) position (u=(x+1)/2, v=(z+1)/2),
# so the cap renders as an undistorted octagon instead of a flattened strip.
# The 8 side quads each get their own full (0,0)-(1,0)-(1,1)-(0,1) unit
# square, one per face, so no two side faces (even adjacent ones sharing an
# edge) share a draggable UV point.
